Key Match Events: Merih Demiral scored in each half to guide Turkey to a 2-1 victory
Michael Gregoritsch scored Austria's goal in the 66th minute
Christoph Baumgartner's header was saved by a stunning one-handed save from Gunok in the final seconds
Post-Match Reflections: Turkey coach Vincenzo Montella described the match as important and historic
Austria coach Ralf Rangnick said the team tried everything and had chances to score but lacked luck
Rangnick mentioned that if the game went to extra time, Austria would have had a chance to win
Miscellaneous Highlights: Merih Demiral was the goal-scoring hero for Turkey
The match ended in heavy rain
Turkey booked their spot in Euro 2024's last eight with a 2-1 victory over Austria
Austria is still waiting for their first win in a knockout match at any major tournament since 1954
